de.spricom.dessert.resolve

Class ClassEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.spricom.dessert.resolve.ClassEntry

  • public abstract class ClassEntry
extends Object
    A ClassEntry represents a single class file within one classes directory or .jar file. It's linked to the ClassPackage it belongs to. If there is an other .class file with the same name in some other classes directory or .jar file within the ClassResolver scope it has a reference to a list of all such .class files.

      • getClassfile

        public ClassFile getClassfile()
        Resolves the ClassFile by analyzing the byte code. This is a time consuming operation and should be called as late as possible. For .jar files the most time is spent by decompressing the .class file. The result will be cached for further calls.
        Returns:
        a chached or frechly resolved instance of the ClassFile
